FIX — Replace DALL-E 3 / OpenAI dependency with OpenRouter's Image API

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
CONTEXT
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Step 67 was originally built against OpenAI's DALL-E 3 directly, using
settings.OPENAI_API_KEY. That's being scrapped — this project should
use ONLY OpenRouter for all AI calls (text already goes through
OpenRouterProvider/ProviderManager). Images should go through
OpenRouter's Image API instead of a direct OpenAI dependency.

OpenRouter now has a dedicated Image API (separate from chat
completions): POST https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/images, using the
same OPENROUTER_API_KEY already funded and working for text. It
supports 30+ image models (Google Gemini image models, Black Forest
Labs FLUX, ByteDance Seedream, OpenAI's GPT Image via OpenRouter,
xAI Grok Imagine, etc.) through one unified request/response shape,
with images returned as base64.

Before writing any code, fetch and read
https://openrouter.ai/docs/guides/overview/multimodal/image-generation
directly — do not rely on assumed knowledge of the request/response
schema, since this is a newer API surface. Also fetch
https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/images/models?output_modalities=image
to see current available models and their capabilities, and (once
you've picked a model) fetch
https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/images/models/{model_id}/endpoints
to get that model's exact accepted parameters, supported aspect
ratios, and pricing — per-model details differ (e.g. some support 18
aspect ratios, others 14; some cap at 1 image per call).

DEFAULT MODEL CHOICE: use "google/gemini-3.1-flash-image" (marketed
as "Nano Banana 2") as the default — strong quality-to-speed ratio,
reasonable cost, wide aspect-ratio support, base64 output natively.
Make this configurable (see settings change below) so it can be
swapped later without code changes.

