STEP 1 — Replace the image provider implementation
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

- Delete app/core/providers/dalle3_provider.py (or rename/repurpose —
  your call, but it must no longer be what's registered/used).
- Create app/core/providers/openrouter_image_provider.py implementing
  a new OpenRouterImageProvider(BaseImageProvider) class:
    - Reads OPENROUTER_API_KEY the same way OpenRouterProvider does
      (settings or os.getenv fallback — match the existing pattern in
      app/core/providers/openrouter_provider.py).
    - Constructor raises a clear error immediately if the key is
      missing, same fail-loud behavior the DALL-E provider had.
    - generate_image() calls POST https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/images
      with the model, prompt, and any size/aspect-ratio parameter that
      endpoint actually accepts (confirm this from the docs fetch
      above — do not guess field names).
    - Parses the base64 image data out of the actual response shape
      (confirm exact field names from the docs/endpoint fetch, don't
      assume it matches the old DALL-E response shape) and returns an
      ImageGenerationResult with b64_data populated (url likely None
      since this API returns base64, not hosted URLs — confirm this
      too).
    - Self-registers with ImageProviderManager under the name
      "openrouter" on import, same self-registration pattern the old
      dalle3_provider.py used.
  Do NOT modify app/core/providers/image_base.py or
  app/core/providers/image_manager.py — the abstraction itself is
  correct and provider-agnostic; only the concrete provider changes.

